@Doug 

The only martinis I made when I still made martinis were always gin, never vodka, about 30% vermouth, with a high quality olive and a dash or two of olive brine.

My wife and I do not like vodka - over here it is the most popular liquor, drunk to excess on every occasion. Not only is the taste meh, but all I see when I think "vodka" are rowdy, sweaty men (their soaked shirts partly out of their belts), singing badly, cursing, vomiting and possibly wetting themselves.

@David Johnson 

