@RozzieGrandma 

FAKIE is used in snowboarding, too. I took one snowboarding lesson (after many years of skiing) and the first thing they do is determine your natural stance. That stance is what you’d use almost all the time. 

My snowboarding husband says he rides FAKIE about 1% of the time.

@RozzieGrandma 
I'm going deep into the weeds here. I am what is called a goofy foot, which means I prefer my dominant foot forward on a skateboard/snowboard/wakeboard, whereas most prefer it the other way, to better steer the board with the back foot. This is probably because I learned to waterski with the stronger foot forward, to help launch from the water. But if you're going FAKIE, it means you're switching to your less-preferred stance, or weakside, which means any trick you attempt will be harder to pull off.

For the record, I have surfed exactly once, and that was when I was stationed in Monterey - we could get boards and wetsuits at the Fort Ord Morale rec center.

